<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Typhoon Paka Strikes Guam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Typhoon Paka struck
northern Guam today, causing injuries and major damage, reports
reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The eye of the storm crossed over the northern tip of Guam by 8
p.m. (5 a.m. EST), causing heavy damage and some flooding along
low-lying coastal areas.
</P>
<P>
Local fire department said that the houses were flying, three
people were reported injured when their houses collapsed on top of
them. The total number of injuries could not be known immediately.
</P>
<P>
The storm reached the U.S. territory packing maximum sustained
winds of 240 kph and gusts of more than 280 kph, the National
Weather Service said.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of people were forced to leave their homes for
emergency shelters in schools.
</P>
<P>
The island was without electricity. Television signals from the
island were shut down hours before the storm, and most of the
radio stations on the island lost their ability to transmit.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
