<HEADLINE> French PM to Visit Morocco </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 16 (Xinhua) -- French Prime Minister Lionel
Jospin will pay an official visit to Morocco from Wednesday, his
first to a non-European country since he took office in June.
</P>
<P>
Jospin will be accompanied by several of his cabinet ministers
and a delegation of French businessmen. He will meet King Hassan
II and Prime Minister Abdellatif Filali, according to Agence
France-Presse (AFP).
</P>
<P>
Franco-Moroccan relations are now marked by great economic
interdependence and cooperation in culture, science and technology.
</P>
<P>
France is the biggest trade partner of Morocco, buying 27
percent of its export products.
</P>
<P>
France cancelled 400 million francs (67 million U.S. dollars)
of debts owed by Morocco in October and turned other debts into
new loans. It has provided annual aid of one billion franc (17
million U.S. dollars) to the country over the past five years.
</P>
<P>
Jospin will also visit Senegal and Mali in his African tour.
</P>
</TEXT>
