<HEADLINE> Pakistan Acting President Calls for Human Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Acting President of Pakistan
Wasim Sajjad today stressed the need for giving due importance to
the human resources development in member countries of the
Organization of the Islamic Conference (OIC).
</P>
<P>
Addressing a meeting of the OIC Ministerial Standing Committee
on Scientific and Technological Cooperation, Wasim said there was
a dire need for creating a highly trained and experienced group
within individual member states.
</P>
<P>
He said the meeting offered an appropriate opportunity to
review the past achievements and failures, and to evaluate new
initiatives.
</P>
<P>
Vigorous and sustained efforts have been made to build a strong
and highly-motivated scientific community in the Muslim world,
said Wasim, adding that high priority is being given to the human
resources development.
</P>
<P>
Wasim said an organization titled "the International Forum for
Science, Technology and Human resources Development" had been
established recently.
</P>
<P>
The prime objectives of the forum are to foster human resources
among Muslim societies and create facilities and opportunities
among Muslim intellectuals to exchange views, experiences and
expertise, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
