<HEADLINE> Kohl Pledges Support for Romania's Bid for EU Membership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 16 (Xinhua) -- German Chancellor Helmut Kohl
today told visiting Romanian President Emil Constantinescu that
Germany would do its best to support the country's bid to join the
European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
Under a decision made by the EU leaders during their Luxembourg
summit last weekend, Romania was among the 11 countries mainly
from Eastern and Central Europe which had been invited to join the
15-nation EU.
</P>
<P>
However, other than Estonia, the Czech Republic, Hungary,
Poland, Slovenia and Cyprus, with which the EU would begin
membership talks early next year, Romania and other four nations
were placed on a slower negotiating track to enable them to make
further efforts to meet entry conditions.
</P>
<P>
Stressing that the EU decision bears the concrete prospect for
Romania's admission into the EU, Kohl told Constantinescu that
Germany would make all possible contributions to help the country
meet the conditions for membership negotiations with the EU as
soon as possible, German government spokesman Peter Hausmann said.
</P>
<P>
Constantinescu, who started a three-day visit to Germany today,
also met German President Roman Herzog this morning. He is also
scheduled to address German business leaders in Bonn before
visiting Munich and Hamburg. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
