<HEADLINE> China Signs Market Access Agreements with Turkey, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- China has signed the agreement
on market access in goods with two more countries, bringing the
total number of countries having signed such an agreement to nine.
</P>
<P>
According to Chinese trade delegation sources, China signed the
agreement respectively with Turkey and Singapore during a series
of bilateral talks on China's accession to the World Trade
Organization (WTO) here last week.
</P>
<P>
The other seven countries having signed the agreement with
China are Hungary, the Czech Republic, Slovakia, Japan, Korea,
Pakistan, and New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that China has been having bilateral talks on
market access with 35 WTO members (counting 15 members of the
European Union as one). The talks with around 20 of them are
reaching the final stage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
