<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia National Commercial Bank Begin to Make </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- The Zambia National Commercial
Bank registered a profit before tax of 1.27 billion Kwacha (about
one million U.S. Dollars) during the financial year ending on
March 31, 1997, Zambia News Agency ZANA reported today.
</P>
<P>
The bank's Managing Director Samuel Musonda was quoted as
saying at a news briefing here today that the bank mamaged to
recover from the huge loss incurred in the previous year
amounting to 8.96 billion Kwacha or about 6.8 million U.S.
Dollars.
</P>
<P>
Musonda explained that the profit recorded in the year under
review is achieved aginst an environment of intensive credit
review, high inflation and stiff competition.
</P>
<P>
He attributed the profit to the bank's restructuring program
under which about 1,000 employees, 42 percent of the total, were
laid off and the conditions of service for the remaining
employees have been improved.
</P>
<P>
He added that the bad performance of the country's weakened
manufacturing and industrial sectors also impacts adversely on
the bank's performance.
</P>
<P>
Musonda also disclosed that the bank's capital still remains
above!the stipulated 2 billion Kwacha (about 1.5 million dollars)
required by the Bank of Zambia to operate a commercial bank.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
