<HEADLINE> Ms Anne Petitpierre Elected ICRC Vice President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Ms Anne Petitpierre, professor at
the Faculty of Law of Geneva University, has been elected vice
president of the International Committee of the Red Cross (ICRC).
</P>
<P>
Ms Petitpierre will replace Pierre Keller, who is retiring from the
ICRC, for a four-year term, according to an ICRC press release here
today.
</P>
<P>
Ms Petitpierre has been a member of the Geneva Bar since 1970 and
has carried out extensive academic research within the Faculty of
Law of Geneva University.
</P>
<P>
She was elected member of the ICRC in 1987 and member of the
executive board in 1989. 
