<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Inflation Rate Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's year-on-year
inflation has risen to 19.4 percent for November, up 3.4
percentage point from the previous month, the Central Statistical
Office (CSO) said today.
</P>
<P>
The Discount House of Zimbabwe said the payment of former
freedom fighters gratuities and pensions as well as the recent
announced increase in the rediscount rate from 28.5 to 31.5
percent to control the run away money supply, continued to exert
pressures on the economy.
</P>
<P>
Raising the rediscount rate was not the solution to the
current economic woes, unless the government first resolves the
economic fundamentals, the rate of inflation would reach
unprecedented levels, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
