<HEADLINE> UK Sports Academy to Be Built in Sheffield, England </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 16 (Xinhua) -- British National Heritage
Secretary Chris Smith announced here today that industrial city of
Sheffield, England, has been chosen as the site for a new British
sports academy.
</P>
<P>
Smith said the government would spend 160 million pounds (about
261 million U.S. dollars) on building the headquarters of the
United Kingdom Sports Institute in Sheffield.
</P>
<P>
"It fires the starting gun for the next stage in a process
which I believe will provide our very best sporting talent with
the facilities and backup to help them challenge and beat the rest
of the world," he said.
</P>
<P>
Smith noted that the national sports center would provide the
best in sports science, medicine, nutrition and coaching
expertise.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that a consortium including Sheffield's two
universities, two hospital trusts and the city council are to
build the institute with funding from the National Lottery.
</P>
</TEXT>
