<HEADLINE> European Shares Rally on Firm Wall Street </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Major stock markets in Europe
all surged strongly and ended sharply higher Tuesday, boosted by a
firm Wall Street and a stronger dollar.
</P>
<P>
Britain's FTSE 100 index finished higher for a third day
running and narrowly below session highs after Wall Street gains
fuelled the market.
</P>
<P>
Stocks in New York rallied on hopes that the Federal Reserve
will leave interest rates unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Fresh bid speculation in London in the banking sector also
lured buyers and exporters were helped by sterling's recent slump.
</P>
<P>
The index ended 81.6 points higher at 5,203.4, the highest
close in two months.
</P>
<P>
German shares in Frankfurt also ended at the day's highs after
the stronger dollar boosted trading, with the DAX-30 index closing
at 4,083.97, up 23.93 points or 0.59 percent.
</P>
<P>
Bullish signals from Wall Street and some Asian markets also
helped market sentiment.
</P>
<P>
In Paris French shares built on gains scored on Monday as
investors returned to the market. Defense shares rose after
Dassault Aviation clinched a two billion US dollars deal with
United Arab Emirates. The CAC-40 index closed at 2,912.18, 73.91
points or 2.6 percent higher. 
</P>
</TEXT>
