<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Annan Appoints His Representative to Liberia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, December 16 (Xinhua) -- UN Secretary-General
Kofi Annan today appointed Felix Downes-Thomas, a national of the
Gambia, to be his representative in Liberia and the Head of the
United Nations Peace Building Support Office in the country.
</P>
<P>
Mr. Downes-Thomas joined the United Nations in 1969, and since
April 1997 had been the Director of the Complex Emergency Division
of the Department of Humanitarian Affairs (DHA), where he had also
served as Deputy Director and participated in the UN/Iraq
negotiations that led to the United Nations Humanitarian Program
in Iraq (oil-for-food).
</P>
<P>
Prior to this, Downes-Thomas had been the Director of the
United Nations Office of Humanitarian Assistance Coordination in
Mozambique from March to December 1994 and from April 1992 to
February 1994 as Deputy Director of the Regional Monitoring
Division of DHA, with specific responsibility for dealing with
humanitarian emergencies in Africa.
</P>
<P>
From 1986 to 1992, he served in the Office of the
Secretary-General, where he dealt with special political affairs.
In this capacity, he served on the Secretary-General's Iran/Iraq
negotiating team and on the Secretary-General's Namibia Task
Force.
</P>
<P>
Downes-Thomas studied political science and international
relations first at Yale University, and then at St. Johns
University in New York.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
