<HEADLINE> Nigeria Records $7.5b Foreign Reserves </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria's foreign reserves has risen
to the current level of 7.5 billion U.S. Dollars, the News Agency of
Nigeria reported today, quoting Finance Minister Anthony Ani.
</P>
<P>
According to Ani, the rate of inflation declined tremendously from
72.8 percent in December 1995 to less than 10 percent by the end of
November this year.
</P>
<P>
With interest rates falling and remaining stable, the minister said
that the distress syndrome in the country's banking system has been
contained and all cases of distressed banks will be finally disposed
of very soon.
</P>
<P>
He also noted the grave situation in which 80 percent of the total
revenue of a state or local government council was devoted to
recurrent expenditure, saying that it was not conducive to the growth.
</P>
<P>
The minister, therefore, urged states and local government councils
to critically review their expenditure pattern and re-order their
priorities so that their activities would have direct impact on the
people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
