<HEADLINE> Daimler-Benz Sells Semiconductor Unit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Germany's largest industrial
group Daimler-Benz AG announced today that it will sell the
semiconductor division of its subsidiary Temic Telefunken to the
U.S. company Vishay Intertechnology Inc. for about 500 million
U.S. dollars by next March.
</P>
<P>
The sale of the still fast-growing and profit-making Temic
semiconductor division would allow Daimler-Benz to focus on its
core businesses directly related to transportation products and
services, the company said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
The Temic group, which described itself as the fourth largest
semiconductor producer in Europe, is expecting total sales of
about 2.6 billion German marks (1.5 billion U.S. dollars) in 1997.
Its products are found in mobile phones, personal computers, as
well as automotive and consumer electronics.
</P>
<P>
However, the automotive electronics division of the Temic group
was excluded from the sale and would remain under the banner of
Daimler-Benz, the company said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
