<HEADLINE> Kuwait Official Optimistic about GCC Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, December 16 (Xinhua) -- A high-ranking Kuwaiti
official said today he is optimistic that the forthcoming summit
of the Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) will yield good results and
strengthen relations in all spheres among the member states.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Sheikh Sabah Al-Ahmad told the official
Kuwait News Agency that the GCC foreign ministers' meeting will
be held here Wednesday to decide the summit agenda.
</P>
<P>
The summit would enhance member nations' march towards unity
and realize the aspirations and interests of their peoples.
</P>
<P>
He said the foreign ministers of Saudi Arabia, Bahrain, Qatar,
the United Arab Emirates, Oman and Kuwait will submit draft
resolutions and recommendations in their final form to their
leaders.
</P>
<P>
He hoped the foreign ministers would "succeed in preparing all
the draft resolutions to facilitate the missions of the summit in
realizing the aspirations of the Gulf peoples."
</P>
<P>
These ministers met in Kuwait for two days late last month to
prepare a draft summit agenda and discuss means of activating
cooperation and coordination in the political, economic, security
and military spheres.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a Kuwaiti organization official said all
arrangements have been made with the coordination of the
information, interior, communication and finance ministries to
ensure the summit a success.
</P>
<P>
The meeting to be held on December 20-22 would be the 18th
summit since the foundation of the regional political, economic
and defense organization in 1981.
</P>
<P>
The GCC leaders held their last meeting in December 1996 in
Doha, Qatar during which they decided to unify custom tariffs and
set up a joint GCC custom union. 
</P>
