<HEADLINE> Canada's Mutual Fund Sales Drop in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Worries over volatile stock
markets produced a 1 billion dollar (0.7 billion US dollar) drop
in Canada's mutual fund sales in November, said reports today.
</P>
<P>
Net sales into all types of mutual funds totaled 4.3 billion
dollars in November, down 18 percent in November 1996.
</P>
<P>
Volatile and declining markets around the world wiped 2.3
percent or 6.43 billion dollars from the total asset value of
mutual funds of the country.
</P>
<P>
Once new sales were added, assets in mutual funds were down
just 0.7 percent at the end of November at 277.7 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
November is typically the fourth-best month for mutual funds of
the year.
</P>
<P>
Because of the volatile markets, Canada is expecting a drop
from last year, the reports said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
