<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Plans Major Reform of Textile Industry (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The enterprises can obtain 5 million yuan: 3 million yuan in
government allocations and 2 million yuan in loans with interests
subsidized by the State for eliminating 10,000 spindles. "All the
capital should be used to develop new products, adjust the product
mix and arrange help for laid-off employees," said a textile
official.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government plans to issue licenses for
manufacturers and sellers of textile machinery to reduce the
number of spindles.
</P>
<P>
Currently, China has 47 million spindles, 12 million of which
are obsolete. This outdated equipment is one more reason for
inefficiencies, the official said.
</P>
<P>
To prevent the eliminated spindles from being installed in other
locations, such as smaller rural mills, the 10 million spindles
removed from service between 1998 and 2000 will be destroyed.
</P>
<P>
Ma Yuliang, director of the management department under the
China National Textile Council, told Xinhua that the financially
troubled textile sector is considered one of China's biggest
headaches in enterprise reform. The government this year allocated
9.73 billion yuan for 555 state textile enterprises to write off
non-performing and bad accounts.
</P>
<P>
"The state plans to project an additional 10 billion yuan in the
regard, of which a larger portion will be used to rejuvenate the
textile sector," he said.
</P>
<P>
Ma said that the central government has lowered cotton
prices this year. The reduced raw-materials cost has effectively
cut losses for the industry. The losses between January and
September this year were 21.3 percent, or 1.78 billion yuan less
than the same period of previous year.
</P>
<P>
Ma said 4.8 million spindles will be reduced in the coastal
provinces and municipalities in 1998, and 600,000 employees be
assigned new jobs. "With the state preferential policy in place
and other effective reform efforts, the sector is set to cut 3
billion yuan of losses next year," Ma said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
