<HEADLINE> Iran's Azizi Named Asian Footballer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Iranian soccer star
Khodadad Azizi, who plays with German club FC Cologne, was named
Wednesday as Asian footballer of the month for November.
</P>
<P>
The Asian Football Confederation (AFC) said Azizi won the award
for his two goals against Australia that took Iran to the World
Cup finals for the first time in 20 years.
</P>
<P>
Japan's Takeshi Okada won the coach of the month award for his
role in getting Japan to the finals for the first time.
</P>
<P>
Okada, who took over from the sacked Shu Kamo only at the
beginning of October, secured a precious victory over South Korea
in Seoul that reopened the door to the World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia, who have reached the finals for their second
straight time, were named as the best team of the month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
