<HEADLINE> Overseas Pakistanis to Hold Conference in Islamabad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 17 (Xinhua) -- A first-ever conference of
elected representatives of Pakistanis residing in other countries
will be held here Thursday aimed at promoting their participation
in their motherland's development programs.
</P>
<P>
More than 70 overseas Pakistanis, most of them from the United
Kingdom, will attend the conference which is expected to be
inaugurated by Acting President Wasim Sajjad, the official
Associated Press of Pakistan (APP) said today.
</P>
<P>
The conference is a very important initiative of the government
to increase the role of overseas Pakistanis in the country's
development by giving them a sense of participation, Parliamentary
Secretary for Information Anwarul Haq Ramay was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Working groups in different areas to develop linkages and
undertake economic development programs will be formed at the
conference, Ramay said.
</P>
<P>
He also said efforts will be made to utilize the experience and
expertise of overseas Pakistanis and their views will be
considered in policy making.  
</P>
</TEXT>
