<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Vows to Maintain Sustainable Economic Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zou
Jiahua has urged the country to step up strategic adjustments to
the economy to maintain sustainable, rapid, sound development.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier's remarks came at the National Conference on
Planning which was held here Dec. 13-16.
</P>
<P>
He said China has maintained a sustained and rapid economic
development in recent years while holding the line on prices.
</P>
<P>
Agriculture has had several good years in a row, and the
bottleneck in the sectors of energy and communications has been
eased. Domestic savings also have remained at a relatively high
level. All these factors have contributed to sustained and rapid
economic development, the vice-premier added.
</P>
<P>
He urged various localities to take a moderate path in
investment growth, optimize investment structure, expand exports
and vigorously tap international markets.
</P>
<P>
Zou said priority should be given to re-employment,
establishment and perfection of the social security system,
deepening reform in grain and cotton circulation systems, and the
industrialization of agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The coastal and advanced areas should support economic
development in the vast central and western parts of the country,
he said, to narrow economic disparity.  
</P>
</TEXT>
