<HEADLINE> EF Language Leads Again </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Leg one winner EF Language
grabbed the lead in the third stage of the Whitbread Round the
World Race on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
American skipper of the Swede EF Language, Paul Cayard, said
early on Wednesday that they had stayed on the same track for an
easier 12 hours.
</P>
<P>
Dennis Conner's Toshiba lost his yesterday's lead and slipped
 to third place behind Swedish Match.
</P>
<P>
The EF Language is now 1,274 miles from Sydney, the next
stopover, and sailing in 10 knot southerly winds.
</P>
<P>
The fleet are now half way across the Great Australian Bight,
but spread over a front of about 120 miles, on a north-south line,
and split into three groups.
</P>
<P>
The day of reckoning will come when the fleet reaches Bass
Straight, before turning north up the east coast of Australia.
</P>
</TEXT>
