<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Marken Wins in First Leg of Downhill Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Norwigian Ingeborg Marken won
the first leg of a women's alpine skiing downhill race in Val
d'Isere, Italy, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Marken, 22, defeated the race favorite Katja Seizinger of
Germany, posting the fastest time of one minute and 59 seconds.
</P>
<P>
This is the second World Cup victory for the Norwegian who
previously won in a Super-G last year in Lillehammer.
</P>
<P>
World Cup leader Seizinger, who has won the last four speed
events this season with two downhill and two Super-G titles,
clocked 1:01.61, followed by compatriot Hilde Gerg with 0.01
seconds behind in a shortened piste for bad weather.
</P>
<P>
Former world champion Picabo Street of Sweden finished 10th
with a time of 1:02.34, while fellow Pernilla Wiberg, another
downhill champion, wound up a disappointing 1:03.28. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
