Congress had made new breakthroughs theoretically in
state-enterprise reform.
</P>
<P>
The CPC Central Committee and the State Council have pinned
high hopes on 1998, the first year of three for realizing
the strategic goals of enterprise reform.
</P>
<P>
The issue of re-employment for those laid off from state-run
factories should be given great significance, he said. Measures
will be taken to curb illegal charges and levies on enterprises
next year, he added. 
