<HEADLINE> Assoc. for Firms Funded by Other Areas Set Up in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Enterprises with sole
investment from other parts of the country established an
association of their own in Shanghai today. So far, 2,750 firms
have become association members.
</P>
<P>
The association will play the role to link up these members and
will also act as a bridge between these firms and the municipal
government, said Jiang Guangyu, Chairman of the body and also a
deputy secretary general of the municipal government.
</P>
<P>
According to Vice-Mayor Zhao Qizheng, the number of companies
set up in Shanghai by investors from other areas has approached
10,500.
</P>
<P>
These firms, which have a total capital of 24.9 billion yuan
and employ 85,500 local residents, have become major tax-payers
for the city, he said. 
