<HEADLINE> Salas No Intention to Join Manchester United </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Chilean international striker
Marcello Salas turned down an offer of Manchester United to move
to the champions of the English Premier League, his agent said on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Gustavo Moscardi, the agent of the Salas, told the Sun, the
English tabloid newspaper, "Marcello has no intention of moving to
Manchester United now. That's a decision reached by the player,
his family and myself."
</P>
<P>
United has been seeking to recruit the player, who plays for
River Plate in Argentina, for a couple of months.
</P>
<P>
The 22-year-old Salas seems poise to move to Italian Serie A
clubs, with Parma and Lazio the most favorites.
</P>
<P>
Salas, who was described as "a very good player" by United
manager Alex Ferguson, has 31 caps and scored 11 goals in 12 games
in the South American World Cup Zone qualifiers. 
