<HEADLINE> Macao Countdown Forum Calls for Active Participation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Macao residents should make
earnest efforts to create a better future in the coming two years
before the handover of power, said participants in a forum.
</P>
<P>
Many participants in a forum Tuesday night on the two year
countdown of Macao's return to the motherland said that Macao
residents should make it their own duty to build a better Macao.
</P>
<P>
"Time is running out and there remains a lot to do for a smooth
handover of power in the coming two years," said Tang Chou Kei,
editor-in-chief of the Va Kio newspaper.
</P>
<P>
Business people, he said, should expand their business in Macao
rather than anywhere else. They should make it their duty to turn
Macao into a better place after the establishment of the Macao
Special Administrative Region (SAR) in December 1999, he added.
</P>
<P>
Tang's ideas were widely echoed at the forum, which was
attended by more than 50 people representing different social
groups. The forum was organized by the Macao Basic Law Promotion
Association.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, some participants proposed that the Preparatory
Committee for the Macao SAR be established as soon as possible to
encourage Macao residents' participation in social and
transitional affairs.
</P>
<P>
Most participants are optimistic about Macao's future.
</P>
<P>
"Facts show that Hong Kong remains stable and its economy
prospers after its return to China," said Li Po Tin, chairman of
the Macao Coca Cola Company. "Today's Hong Kong will be tomorrow's
Macao. I am convinced that Macao will return smoothly."  
</P>
</TEXT>
