<HEADLINE> Philippine Garments Exports Up by 6 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Philippine garments and textile
exports during the first 11 months of the year soared by 6 percent
to 2.71 billion U.S. dollars from last year's 2.56 billion
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Data released by the Garments and Textile Export Board
Wednesday shows that the United States remained the biggest market
for the Philippines with a purchase of 1.7 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
