<HEADLINE> Iraq to Operate Road Passenger Transport to Syria, </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Iraq will begin to operate
direct passenger transport services by road to Syria and Iran next
year, the Iraqi newspaper "Al-Thawara" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Iraq and Syria have agreed to open the road transport line
linking the two neighbors' capitals Baghdad and Damascus, Iraqi
General Passenger Transport Organization Director General Yehyia
Khedr Al-Ani told the newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The organization is responsible for managing passenger
transport along the line, said Al-Ani.
</P>
<P>
He added that his organization also is ready to operate an
identical service linking Baghdad and the Iranian capital Tehran
next year, which will carry Iranian visitors to holy sites in
Iraq. 
</P>
</TEXT>
