<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets Krupp Company Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Zou
Jiahua met here this afternoon with Gerhard Cromme, chairman of
the board of directors of the Krupp Company.
</P>
<P>
Crupp is Germany's biggest non-ferrous metals supplier as well
as one of the world's leading flat steel suppliers.
</P>
<P>
Zou also was present at a signing ceremony marking the
establishment of Shanghai-Krupp Stainless Steel Corp., a joint
venture between Krupp-Thyssen Stainless Co., Ltd. and Shanghai
Pudong Iron and Steel Group.
</P>
<P>
The joint venture will produce cold-rolled sheet steel. The
project, with an investment of 1.4 billion U.S. dollars, will use
the world's advanced technology in steel manufacturing. Its
designed annual production capacity is 440,000 tons of rolled
stainless steel.
</P>
<P>
Zou congratulated participants on the signing of the project on
behalf of the Chinese government. He said Sino-German relations
have grown smoothly in recent years, which helped promote
cooperation in relevant sectors.
</P>
<P>
He said Krupp, founded in 1811, has maintained cooperation with
China for a long time and the launching of the new project marks a
new stage.
</P>
<P>
Cromme thanked the governments of China and Shanghai for their
support. He said his company will continue promoting the
development of friendly relations and cooperation between Germany
and China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
