<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Gains 74.39 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 17 (Xinhua)-- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) gained 74.39 points to 3487.02
Wednesday as against Tuesday's close of 3424.87.
</P>
<P>
The national index rose by 24.84 points to 1514.69 from the
previous close of 1489.85.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and U.S. dollar indexes were quoted up at 338.22
and 142.70 compared with the previous close of 332.59 and 140.40
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Share prices made headway pushing the sensitive index sharply
up by more than 74 points on the BSE market in the wake of
sustained and heavily speculative buying coupled with fresh
negligible purchases by financial institutions and foreign funds.
 
</P>
