<HEADLINE> House Speaker, Better Presidential Candidate: Ramos </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel
Ramos said on Wednesday that House of Representatives Speaker Jose
de Venecia still has a better chance of winning next year's
presidential elections than other presidential candidates.
</P>
<P>
"(De Venecia is still) better than the others," Ramos said
during a press conference held in the Presidential Palace when
asked about his assessment on de Venecia's chances of winning
after former defense secretary Renato de Villa bolted the ruling
party and formed "a third force" with Manila Mayor Alfredo Lim.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Ramos reiterated his advice for de Villa to
reconsider his decision.
</P>
<P>
"I hope that Renato de Villa and his followers will reexamine
their position in the light of their participation in and
commitments to the party's political processes and as well as the
chances of their success outside the administration party," Ramos
said.
</P>
<P>
He added that the former defense secretary will be welcomed by
the Lakas-NUCD party if ever he decides to rejoin "because
reconciliation has always been a major policy thrust of the Ramos
administration."
</P>
<P>
Ramos disclosed that one factor he anointed de Venecia as the
ruling party's standard bearer in next year's presidential polls
was the speaker's capability of continuing the economic, social
and political reforms of the Ramos administration.  
</P>
</TEXT>
