<HEADLINE> China's NPC Standing Committee to Meet on Dec 27 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The 29th meeting of the
Standing Committee of the Eighth National People's Congress (NPC),
China's top legislature, will be held here from December 24 to 29.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made today at a conference held at the Great
Hall of the People in Beijing, which was attended by the chairman
and vice-chairmen of the NPC Standing Committee. It was presided
over by NPC Standing Committee Chairman Qiao Shi.
</P>
<P>
Participants to the upcoming 29th meeting will examine drafts
of laws concerning blood donation, pricing, the prevention and
alleviation of earthquakes, and higher education.
</P>
<P>
Members of the NPC Standing Committee will discuss a bill on
convening the First Session of the Ninth National People's
Congress, and another bill on drafting a law on the country's new
and high-tech industrial zones.
</P>
<P>
The participants will also hear reports on the country's
financial situation and on inspections over the implementation of
laws concerning agriculture and water resources.
</P>
<P>
Speaking about the election of deputies from the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region to the Ninth NPC, Cao Zhi,
secretary-general of the NPC Standing Committee, said that the
election was conducted in strict accordance with the law and
democratic procedure, and the election process is open and just.
</P>
</TEXT>
