<HEADLINE> Beijing Elects New Party Leadership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 17 (Xinhua)-- Jia Qinglin was elected
secretary of the Beijing Municipal Committee of the Chinese
Communist Party at the First Plenary Session of the Eighth Beijing
Municipal Party Committee held here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The 57-year old Jia was appointed the capital city's Party
secretary in August this year by the CPC Central Committee. He has
also served as Beijing mayor since February this year.
</P>
<P>
The first plenum also elected the new Party leadership of
Beijing, which includes a 13-member standing committee and four
deputy secretaries, of the municipal Party committee.
</P>
<P>
The Eighth Beijing Congress of the CPC closed here this
morning. During the six-day congress, the deputies reviewed
Beijing's work over the past five years and worked out the city's
development strategies for the coming five years. 
</P>
