<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Youngsters Poor on World War Two History </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Most French primary school
children and many high school students do not know well the
history of World War II, French children's daily Mon Quotidien
reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In a poll conducted in November among 800 school children and
students from the age of 10 to 15, the Mon Quotidien posed
questions such as: Do you know what a concentration camp is? Do
you know what a Nazi is? Do you know what a collaborator is?
</P>
<P>
Seventy-six percent of the children and 46 percent of the
students do not know what a concentration camp is, while 92
percent of the children and 66 percent of the students do not know
what Nazi is.
</P>
<P>
The poll also shows that 93 percent of the children and 80
percent of the students do not know what a collaborator is, 60
percent of the children and 33 percent of the students do not know
who a Jew is, and 59 percent of the children and 30 percent of the
students do not know who Hitler is. 
</P>
</TEXT>
