<HEADLINE> Share Prices Rally on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Share prices rallied on the
Singapore market as the benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index
(STII) recovered by 7.76 points to close at 1569.51 points on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The higher finish overnight on Wall Street, some stability in
the regional financial markets, especially in Japan, and
bargain-hunting lifted prices of some blue chips, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
One institutional dealer said that there was some sympathy
buying during the day, as the market had come down so much.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume stood at 187.67 million units, valued
at 311.61 million Singapore dollars (186.59 million US dollars).
Declines continued to lead advances by 205 to 120, while 283 other
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
M. Resources was the most actively traded counter as it
registered a turnover of 13.5 million units. It was followed by
Hotung which had 10.76 million shares traded. The Singapore
Technologies Engineering was next with 9.6 million shares changed
hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it rose by five dollars to finish at 33.5 Singapore
dollars. DBS (Development Bank of Singapore) Foreign increased by
70 cents to end at 14.5 Singapore dollars, while OCBC (Overseas
Chinese Banking Corporation) Foreign picked up by 60 cents to
close at 9.7 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, H Royal was the biggest loser as it declined
by 30 cents to end at 1.3 Singapore dollars. Bukit Sembawang and
the Singapore Airlines 200 fell by 20 cents to finish at 11.1 and
7.65 Singapore dollars respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
