<HEADLINE> India to Launch First Ocean Satellite Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 17 (Xinhua) -- India plans to launch its
first satellite to gather ocean data next year, the Department of
Ocean Development (DOD) sources said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The ocean satellite is expected to collect data with
large-scale applications in fish productivity forecast, ship
routing and coastal pollution monitoring.
</P>
<P>
The ocean satellite will be equipped with a color monitor and
multi-spectral scanning microwave radiometer.
</P>
<P>
The color monitor will gauge concentrations of microscopic
marine plants called phytoplankton, ocean current, pollution and
sedimentation.
</P>
<P>
The microwave radiometer will generate sea surface temperature
data and study ocean-air interactions to help weather forecast.
</P>
</TEXT>
