<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia has received a second
ferry funded by the Danish government, the Mekong River Commission
said here today.
</P>
<P>
The 320-ton deadweight ship, named "Vishnu," was handed over to
the Cambodian government as part of the Danish-funded project on
the upgrading of the ferry facilities in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
The ferry will be used to transport people and goods between
the west and east of Cambodia toward Laos, the commission said in
a press release.
</P>
<P>
