the Mekong River Commission to provide 18 million U.S. dollars to
help upgrade ferry facilities in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
The project included construction of two new ferries,
rehabilitation of three others and construction of new ferry
landings.
</P>
<P>
The first Danish-funded ferry, named "Ta Prohm," was handed
over to the Cambodian government in March this year.  
