<HEADLINE> 20 Kilograms of Hashish Seized in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Turkish police have seized 20
kilograms of hashish in eastern province of Van, the semi-official
Anatolia News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Acting on a tip-off, the Turkish police stopped a bus near Van
airport bound for Istanbul, Turkey's largest city, and found the
hashish hidden under the seat of the second driver of the bus.
</P>
<P>
Five suspects were arrested in connection with the drug
trafficking, said the report, which did not give the date of
police's action.
</P>
<P>
Turkey is the key transit route of drug to Europe from the
"Golden Crescent" area bordering Afghanistan, Iran and Pakistan.
In 1996, Turkey seized 4.4 tonnes of heroin, 12.3 tonnes of
hashish, 233 kilograms of opium, 13 kilograms of cocaine and 1,157
kilograms of base morphine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
