<DOCNO> XIE19971217.0176 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Internet Benefits Chinese University </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Since the campus network of
the University of Science and Technology of China (USTC) with 30
sub-networks went on line in 1995, 70 percent of total computers
in the university have so far been hooked up with Internet,
including over 30 service units and more than 1,600 small
computers, work stations and terminals.
</P>
<P>
The network utilization in the USTC, one of China's most famous
universities based in east China's Anhui province, topped all the
other universities in China.
</P>
<P>
Over the past two years, Internet has promoted the cooperation
and exchanges between USTC and its international counterparts.
</P>
<P>
Through Internet, Chu Yaoquan, director of USTC's Astrophysics
Research Center, participated in some international research
programs such as the design of "Large Sky Area Multi-Object Fiber
Spectrum Scopy Telescope" which involved hundreds of domestic and
overseas scientists and engineers.
</P>
<P>
"Without Internet, it's unimaginable that we can undertake such
a state-of-art work." Professor Chu said.
</P>
<P>
He said that they often conduct on-line discussions with their
overseas partners on Internet, which ensures the smooth progress
of the program.
</P>
<P>
On-line discussions have also helped USTC and its long-term
cooperation partner, Japan High Energy Physics Research
Institution, increase their academic cooperation. When Japanese
counterparts worked at USTC, they can manage their work in Japan
through Internet.
</P>
<P>
With the aid of Internet, USTC has overcome its inadequacy in
some scientific apparatus in research. China's National
Synchrontron Radiation Lab based in USTC, now is able to analyze
its research data effectively on its American counterpart's
computers via Internet.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Internet has become a major information channel to
researchers in USTC and stepped up their pace with the latest
academic development.
</P>
<P>
In disciplines of astrophysics, nuclear physics and information
science, researchers extracted an average of some 300 updated
scientific abstracts per month from data bases on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
USTC President Tang Honggao said that his university will
respond to the latest research development in the world within no
more than three months.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, using Internet to select textbooks and to seek the
suggestions from academic authorities at home and abroad in
setting curriculums resulted in improvement in USTC's teaching and
research programs.
</P>
<P>
In the coming three years, USTC is to invest 7 million yuan in
its computer webs so that it will make full use of Internet and
campus web resources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
