<HEADLINE> Paris Has First Snowfall Before Christmas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Paris Wednesday had its first
snowfall before this Christmas of more than two centimeters
high covering most of the capital region.
</P>
<P>
The Departmental Direction of Equipment (DDE), which is in
charge of snow-clearing, began to clear the main axis this
morning, but most of the secondary roads remain extremely slippery
and several accidents took place, local media reported.
