<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Parents Warned Against Overweight Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese health experts are
cautioning young parents about the calorie and fat of their
infants because the incidence of obesity among Chinese children is
on the rise.
</P>
<P>
A study in Shanghai showed that 4.25 percent of the children in
the 0-6 age group are overweight, and half of the overweight
children suffer from high blood pressure.
</P>
<P>
Their parents' ignorance about a balanced diet is a major cause
of obesity in children, according to today's "Wenhui Daily", which
carries the results of the study. It found that most parents did
not regard their children as being "overweight".
</P>
<P>
Experts warn that overweight children have a higher
tendency to have cerebral problems, diabetes, high blood pressure,
and heart disease.
</P>
<P>
About 70 million Chinese, mostly city dwellers, are obese and
the number is on the rise as people's standard of living has
improved in recent years. Many people put on the unwanted pounds
because they do not do regular exercise, or sleep too much, and
eat food that is high in fat and calories, experts say.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
