<HEADLINE> Myanmar Leader Back From ASEAN Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Chairman of the Myanmar State
Peace and Development Council (SPDC) and Prime Minister Senior
General Than Shwe returned here today after attending the second
ASEAN Informal Summit held in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
While in Kuala Lumpur, Than Shwe also attended an Informal East
Asian Summit and separate Summit Meetings between ASEAN and China,
Japan and South Korea.
</P>
<P>
Than Shwe also had separate bilateral meetings with leaders of
some countries as well as Secretary General of the United Nations
Kofi Annan.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time for the Myanmar top leader to attend a
summit meeting of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations
(ASEAN) since Myanmar was admitted into the grouping in July along
with Laos.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN groups Brunei, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, the
Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.  
</P>
</TEXT>
