<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Reports Success In Changing Oil Development Focus (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, December 17 (Xinhua) -- China's Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region will maintain an annual growth rate of 13.5
percent in oil production and will produce 16.47 million tons of
crude and 2.1 billion cu.m. of gas this year, according to a local
official.
</P>
<P>
Shu Liang, who is in charge of co-ordinating oil production in
the Tarim, Junggar and Turpan-Hami basins in the region, said
Xinjiang has become a key oil production base with rapid increases
in proven oil reserves and crude oil output, and the region is now
making up for the decreases in oil production in the eastern part of
the country.
</P>
<P>
A recent oil and gas report said that the three basins, which
are 740,000 sq.km. in size, have 35.7 billion tons of petroleum
and 2.2 billion cu.m. of gas, accounting for 30 percent and 34
percent of the country's total respectively.
</P>
<P>
The oil industry of China, which now produces more than 140
million tons of crude oil a year, has been stymied by inadequate
oil reserves. In the eastern part, which provides 80 percent of
the country's oil output, the oil reserves have been declining by
20 million tons annually, and oil production costs in some
oilfields have risen rapidly.
</P>
<P>
So, China has turned to its western areas for new resources,
beginning in the early 1990s, and oil-gas exploration in the
three basins has entered a prosperous period thanks to the efforts of
the 100,000 oil workers in Xinjiang.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971217.0196 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2 Dead in Kenyan Election Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Two Kenyans have been killed
with 62 injured and 50 arrested over election-related violence
countrywide since November 15, local press reported today, 12
days before the poll which will take place on December 29.
</P>
<P>
The dead included a woman killed in Mathira Constituency
during a clash between supporters for the ruling Kenya African
National Union party and the Democratic Party, and an
unidentified person killed in Githunguri in similar
circumstances.
</P>
<P>
A total of 78 incidents of violence were reported during the
period, said Deputy Commissioner of Police Geoffrey Mwathe
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Among the injured were four security personnel.
</P>
<P>
Nairobi has the highest number of arrests at 24, followed by
Nyanza Province at 18, Coast six, Central Province five, Rift
Valley four and Western three, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he discounted claims that most of those arrested
were opposition supporters, saying the suspects came from all
political parties.
</P>
<P>
The police is dealing with violence firmly and impartially, he
stressed.
</P>
<P>
"Violence affects everyone, the innocent and the culprits. In
the end, the election will not be free and fair. If we believe in
democracy, we should not encourage violence," Election Commission
Chairman Samuel Kivuitu also emphasized Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Nine of the 15 presidential candidates had requested and been
given round-the-clock security. Those who have not applied
include aspirants from FORD-People, Kenya, UPPK, FORD-Asili and
Umma.
</P>
<P>
Incumbent Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi, 74 and in power
for 19 years, is widely expected to win his last campaign with
five-year more tenure largely due to the division of the
opposition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971217.0197 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Reports Success in Changing Oil Development Focus (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Oil and gas exploration by the China National Petroleum and Gas
Corporation has led to the discovery of 28 industrial oil-bearing
structures and ten gas fields in the Tarim Basin, and 4.4 million
tons of crude oil is expected to be produced there this year, a
rise of 42 percent over last year.
</P>
<P>
A gas exploration team from the Ministry of Geology and Mineral
Resources has discovered in the northern part of the Tarim Basin a
gas field with a production capacity equivalent to 370,000 tons of
oil.
</P>
<P>
Oil and gas exploration in the Karamay Oilfield in the Junggar
Basin has expanded, and four major oilfields, each with 100
million tons of oil reserves, have been found.
</P>
<P>
Oil output in Karamay has been increasing by 400,000 tons a
year and will reach 8.7 million tons this year, maintaining its
position as China's fourth largest oilfield.
</P>
<P>
Oil exploration in the Turpan-Hami Basin started much later but
developed quickly, and, in the past seven years, 20,000 oil workers
have discovered seven industrial oil-bearing structures and 14 oil
and gas fields in the basin, with an annual capacity of 3.5
million tons of crude oil and 900 million cu.m. of natural gas.
</P>
<P>
Local sources say that the basin will be able to produce three
million tons of crude oil and supply Urumqi, the capital of
Xinjiang, with 600 million cu.m. of gas this year for
urea production.
</P>
<P>
According to the China National Petroleum and Gas Corporation,
China has planned to find four billion tons of oil reserves and
510 billion cu.m. of natural gas resources, and produce 23
million tons of crude oil and three billion cu.m. of gas in the
three basins by the end of the century.
</P>
<P>
By then, Xinjiang's oil will account for 20 percent of China's
total output, compared to the present 11 percent.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971217.0198 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Senior Citizens Receive Special Treatment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, December 17 (Xinhua) -- More than 100,000 senior
citizens aged over 60 in Hohhot, capital of north China's Inner
Mongolia Autonomous Region, are enjoying a series of preferential
policies provided by the city's government.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics, people aged over 60 make up about five
percent of the 1.97 million population of the city.
</P>
<P>
Under the policies, the senior citizens may visit the parks,
historic relics, museums and exhibitions free of charge. They are
also given priority in seeing doctors, seeking legal consultations
about old-age pension and subscribing for monthly bus tickets.
</P>
<P>
In addition, more than 3,000 retired veteran cadres in the city
are offered special treatment in shops, banks, post offices, and
on the trains and flights.
</P>
<P>
China will enter an aged society in the year of 2000. Experts
said that people aged at and over 65 will account for seven
percent of the total Chinese population at the turn of the
century.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971217.0199 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader Li Ruihuan Meets Australian FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SYDNEY, Australia, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese
leader Li Ruihuan told Australian Foreign Minister Alexander
Downer here today that China appreciated the efforts made by the
Australian government to promote Sino-Australian relations.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Downer, Li, chairman of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), said the relations as a whole have been
developing smoothly during the past 25 years.
</P>
<P>
A good momentum emerged in the Sino-Australian relations this
year, Li noted.
</P>
<P>
He cited as examples the Australian government's adherence to
the One-China policy, Downer's presence at the swearing-in
ceremony of the Provisional Legislative Council of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region on July 1, and Australia's first
White Paper on Foreign Affairs and Trade issued in August, which
lists Sino-Australian relations as one of its most important
bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
The positions adopted by the Australian government on a series
of major issues have laid a good foundation for the development of
the economic cooperation between the two countries, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Despite the difference in social systems and ideology, China
and Australia are both located in the Asia-pacific region and
share extensive common interests in safeguarding peace and
promoting economic prosperity and development, the Chinese leader
said.
</P>
<P>
"China is confident of the future development of
Sino-Australian relations," he said.
</P>
<P>
Congratulating Downer on his recent successful China visit, Li
said the trip by the foreign minister to China and his
participation in activities marking the 25th anniversary of
Sino-Australian relations had shown the importance the Australian
government attached to the bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
He told Downer that it was one of his aims to have a better
understanding of Australia so as to better learn from the country.
</P>
<P>
Li said creative people should always notice not only the
strong points of its own, but also those of others so as to
improve itself and make constant progress.
</P>
<P>
The failure of a people to notice the good points of its own
would result in a lack of confidence, thus losing the desire to
stand on one's own feet in the world, he said.
</P>
<P>
Losing sight of the strong points of others and always finding
the weak points of others would lead to the failure to remove its
own weakness, improve itself and finally lag behind others, Li
said.
</P>
<P>
Downer said that he agreed with Li, adding the friendly
cooperation between Australia and China has been developing very
rapidly in various fields particularly in economic and trade
fields during the past 25 years since the two countries
established diplomatic ties.
</P>
<P>
The foreign minister said the two countries had also made
successful cooperation on many regional and international issues.
</P>
<P>
Australia hoped the good momentum in the bilateral relations
would continue and was willing to do more in this regard, Downer
said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the Chinese leader also met with representatives of
local Chinese and Australian-Chinese.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
