<HEADLINE> Soldier Killed in Rebel Ambush in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 17 (Xinhua) -- A group of heavily armed rebels
ambushed a patrol jeep today in a mountainous town south of the
capital of Manila, killing a soldier and wounding two policemen.
</P>
<P>
Police said the rebels, belonging to the New People's Army
(NPA), attacked the patrol jeep carrying two policemen and two
army men on a highway in the village of Mabini Ibaba, Macalelon,
Quezon.
</P>
<P>
The rebels immediately withdrew after failing to get the
firearms of the government men, whose comrades fought back and
called in reinforcements, police said.
</P>
<P>
The NPA has fought with the government for more than three
decades and still has a presence in many hinterland areas,
including some rural villages around metropolitan Manila.
</P>
