<HEADLINE> 182 PKK Rebels Killed in Operations in Northern </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Turkish security forces have
killed 182 rebels of the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) in
military operations in northern Iraq since December 5, said an
official statement.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the General Staff of the Turkish Armed
Forces Thursday said the Turkish security forces dealt "a heavy
blow" to the PKK in northern Iraq and ended the operations Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish troops, together with Iraq's Kurdistan Democratic
Party (KDP) forces, launched the cross-border military operations
against the PKK militants in the Hakurk region in northern Iraq on
December 5.
</P>
<P>
There are so far 2,500 or 3,000 PKK guerrillas in northern Iraq
who often launch attacks against civilian and military targets in
Turkey from northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a separatist war in eastern and
southeastern Turkey for autonomy, which has claimed more than
28,000 lives since August 1984. 
