<HEADLINE> China's Electronic Information Industry Developing Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The electronic information
industry has become one of China's fastest growing industry, with
this year's expected industrial output reaching 375 billion yuan
(about 47 billion US dollar), according to a report in the
"Economic Daily".
</P>
<P>
The estimated output will be an increase of 23 percent over
that of last year or 3.6 times that of 1992.
</P>
<P>
With the rapid development of the industry, its technical
renovation capabilities have improved a lot, making great
achievement in scientific research such as one millimeter
super-scale integrated circuit, developing system for big
software, Chinese language operating system, GSM mobile
communication system, etc.
</P>
<P>
