<HEADLINE> Project Brings Hope to Dropouts in Henan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Thanks to the Hope Project,
a nationwide educational drive launched in 1990 in central China's
Henan Province, 296 "Hope" primary schools have been established
and 80,000 dropouts have resumed their education.
</P>
<P>
Henan is China's most populous province, and it has 34
poverty-stricken counties where many children from poor families
drop out education.
</P>
<P>
The local education department has made great efforts to
collect funds and seek donations for the project in the past seven
years. Up to date, the province has collected 44 million yuan
educational funds and received 80 million yuan donations.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the province has set up "Hope" libraries for 310
rural primary schools. 
