<HEADLINE> Unit Cotton Output Sets Record in East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The per hectare output of cotton
in east China's Shandong Province rose to 900 kg this year, a new
record it has set since 1988.
</P>
<P>
The total cotton output of Shandong reached 350 million kg this
year, 22 million kg less than last year's figure as a result of a
big reduction in sowing area.
</P>
<P>
But the province government has allocated six million yuan in
popularizing new cotton varieties and building high-yield
fields. And tangible results were received in this respect.
</P>
<P>
Shandong was the largest cotton producer in China during the
period from 1980 to early 1990s. Its output of cotton used to make
up a quarter of the national total. However, its total and unit
outputs and sowing areas of cotton dropped sharply since late
1980s. The per hectare output even plummeted to 450 kg in 1992.
</P>
</TEXT>
