<HEADLINE> New Edition of Collection of Histories Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 17 (Xinhua) -- A simplified edition of 25
Histories, a collection of 25 most important works on China's
history in modern Chinese has been published in this east China
metropolis.
</P>
<P>
The 25 Histories starting from the Records of the Historian,
authored by Sima Qian (Suema Chien), China's greatest historian in
the first century, is a complete record on China's
five-millennium-old civilization.
</P>
<P>
The new edition, compiled by leading historians across China
and published by Shanghai Ancient Books Publishing House, has 15
volumes with five million Chinese characters.
</P>
<P>
It represents a major step in spreading among the public
knowledge on Chinese history, since previous editions in classical
Chinese are hard to understand for most lay readers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
