<HEADLINE> Macao's Economy Expected To Do Well In Future </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Even though Macao's economy
has lagged behind Chinese inland areas and Hong Kong in recent
years, it is expected to see a turn around through industrial
restructuring, according to some economists.
</P>
<P>
Macao's advantages for economic growth are that it is adjacent
to Hong Kong and Guangdong Province, and that its road, water, and
air transport network, and free port status are good for foreign
investment.
</P>
<P>
Real estate, tourism, banking, and export-oriented
manufacturing have long been four pillar industries, but, because
its economic structure is not so good, its economy slowed down,
economists say. Manufacturing accounted for only 26 percent of the
local output value last year, compared to 36 percent in 1984.
</P>
<P>
Because of other problems in recent years, income from tourism
and gambling, its largest source of government revenues, was also
down a great deal.
</P>
<P>
The government is trying to simplify investment procedures and
improve service to get more foreign investment, and has put
several billion pataca into large scale projects to improve the
investment environment.
</P>
<P>
Funds from inland areas, which are the largest investor in
Macao, have played an important role in economic growth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
