<HEADLINE> Shanghai Volkswagen Cares About Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Volkswagen
Automotive Co.Ltd., a Sino-German joint venture, gives top
priority to the environmental protection and tries to minimize the
harm to the environment during production.
</P>
<P>
One step taken by Volkswagen is to set up a series of rules to
protect the environment such as stipulating that attention must be
paid to the designing of products, technology and package, and
pollution disposal must be restricted.
</P>
<P>
The company provides special training to its employees on the
environmental protection, and about 99 percent of its employees
received the training.
</P>
<P>
It also established special offices to administer affairs
concerning the environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
In order to maintain the sustainable development, the company
has decided to phase out the use of freon, and declared they will
stop using freon on santana cars by the end of the century.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai Volkswagen Company, a joint venture to produce the
Shanghai-Santana cars, is the strongest among China's auto-makers
with an annual production capacity of 300,000 cars. 
