<HEADLINE> Bringing Basic Health Care To Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The government of the Tibet
Autonomous Region will place priority on health care in rural
areas to guarantee basic health care for everyone by the
year 2000.
</P>
<P>
According to regional public health officials, 85 percent of
Tibet's 2.4 million people live in the countryside.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, public health departments have improved
disease prevention and health awareness in rural areas, and major
infectious and endemic diseases have been brought under control.
</P>
<P>
Regional sources say that public health departments will
continue to improve the free medical service in Tibet, which is
central government policy.
</P>
<P>
The region will promote co-operative medical care in rural
areas, officials say. 
</P>
