<HEADLINE> Italy's President Visits Croatia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZAGREB, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Italian President Oscar Luigi
Scalfaro arrived here Tuesday at the invitation of Croatian
President Franjo Tudiman for a two-day state visit to Croatia.
</P>
<P>
After the welcoming ceremony, presided over by Tudiman outside
the presidential residence, the two presidents discussed bilateral
ties, economic cooperation, minority nationality issues, and
Croatia's desire to join the European Union (EU) and the North
Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO).
</P>
<P>
A joint communique will be issued Wednesday after talks between
the two presidents.
</P>
<P>
A military agreement and an oil deal were also signed Tuesday,
which requires the two sides to cooperate on military education
and military training construction. Italy will also provide
Croatia with natural gas worth 4.5 billion U.S. dollars over 24
years.
</P>
<P>
The two countries will build an oil pipeline under the Adriatic
Sea, which will cost 300 million dollars. 
</P>
