<HEADLINE> India's Revenue Department Kicks off Hunting Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 17 (Xinhua)-- India's anti-evasion
directorate has launched nationwide search operations of a "winter
collection drive" for the Revenue Department.
</P>
<P>
Starting with four major automobile manufacturing companies
Tuesday, the directorate is expected to zero in on the white goods
industry in its second round as part of an overall collection
drive, local newspaper Business Standard said today.
</P>
<P>
The Directorate-General of Anti-Evasion (DGAE) Tuesday searched
the offices and factories of four major automobile companies in
the country for alleged excise evasion.
</P>
<P>
The searches were conducted simultaneously in 16 different
centers in the country.
</P>
<P>
According to DGAE sources, the alleged excise evasion relates
to compulsory after-sales services and compulsory warranty
reportedly borne by dealers who were offered high margins by the
automobile companies.
</P>
<P>
"Many more companies will reel under this collection drive,"
said a senior directorate official.  
</P>
</TEXT>
