<DOCNO> XIE19971217.0249 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Finland's Population Hits Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Finland's population reached
a record high of 5.147 million in mid-December, an increase of 0.3
percent over the past year, according to latest data released by
the Finnish Statistics Center.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 60,000 babies were born in 1997, the largest single-year
number since 1973, the Statistics Center. However, Finland's
natural birth rate is still among the lowest in Europe, it said.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, more than 240,000 people have migrated across the
country so far this year, including thousands moving from rural
areas and remote regions to Helsinki, Tampere and other southern
cities.
</P>
<P>
At present, about two million people, or 40 percent of the
country's total population, are living in the province of Uusimaa
around the capital city.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, two-thirds of the country's territory is
uninhabited.
</P>
<P>
This pattern of population distribution not only brings great
pressure on employment, transportation, education and
infrastructure facilities of big cities but also has an
unfavorable impact on the regional balance in development.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19971217.0250 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India to Make WTO Cell Permanent Body </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 17 (Xinhua)-- India's Commerce Ministry is
planning to set up a new International Trade Office in the country
to specially deal with the issues of the World Trade Organization
(WTO) as a permanent body, a government official said here today.
</P>
<P>
The thinking in the government is that there should be a
permanent body to deal with issues related to the WTO which is
governed by several complex agreements contained in the final
Dunkel agreement.
</P>
<P>
At present, the Commerce Ministry looks after all the
agreements with a small team of 4 to 5 persons headed by a single
joint secretary. The team changes all the time with transfers and
promotions of the officers.
</P>
<P>
While the Commerce Ministry is the nodal ministry for WTO
dealings, the agreements require active coordination among
different ministries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
