<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Woman Survives Long Fall Down Elevator Shaft </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cheng Yan was just new to the building on the day there was
some operational failure in the elevator. As she walked toward the
elevator door on the 11th floor, she heard someone talking inside
the shaft, and an elevator repairman who was working in the shaft
asked her to help by holding the door open. As she was trying to
help him, she took a wrong step, lost her balance, and fell into
the empty shaft.
</P>
<P>
When she regained consciousness, Cheng could recall that she
turned several somersaults during the fall, and ended up caught on
the steel elevator cables, hanging upside down.
</P>
<P>
She was declared to be out of danger after an emergency medical
team had a look at her. 
</P>
