<HEADLINE> More Armed Group Members Surrender in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, December 17 (Xinhua) -- A total of 46 more members of
various anti-government armed groups in Myanmar surrendered to the
military last month, official newspaper The New Light of Myanmar
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Those who "exchanged arms for peace" in the northern, western,
north-western, south-eastern and coastal region military command
areas in November, included members of the All Burma Students'
Democratic Front, the Kayin National Union and some other ethnic
armed groups.
</P>
<P>
They brought in some arms and ammunition, the report said.
</P>
<P>
According to a latest official disclosure, a total of 23
anti-government armed groups have made peace with the government,
leaving only two still in insurgency.  
</P>
</TEXT>
