<HEADLINE> Rome to Host U.N. War Crimes Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Rome will host a United Nation
conference on creating a permanent international War Crimes
Tribunal next year, the Italian Foreign ministry said here today.
</P>
<P>
The conference will be held from June 15 to July 17, 1998 and
represents the first "indispensable step" towards the creation of
such a permanent tribunal, Italian Foreign Undersecretary Patrizia
Toia said.
</P>
<P>
She noted that there are many difficult matters which need to
be sorted out at the conference, such as the status of the
tribunal, the types of crimes falling under its jurisdiction and
what powers it is to have, especially if faced with opposition
from countries in which such crimes are perpetrated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
