<HEADLINE> Venezuelan and Nicaraguan Presidents Sign Accords </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Venezuelan President Rafael
Caldera wound up his six-hour visit to Nicaragua Tuesday after
signing several bilateral accords with his host counterpart
Arnoldo Aleman.
</P>
<P>
Among those accords is a cultural exchange agreement aimed at
promoting mutual understanding between the two cultures and paving
the way for cooperation between both countries' educational
institutions.
</P>
<P>
The presidents, on behalf of their foreign affairs ministries,
also signed an agreement to train diplomatic personnel of the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The Nicaraguan president also bestowed on Caldera the "General
Jose Dolores Estrada" medal in recognition of his work in
strengthening the ties and cooperation between both peoples and
governments, which Caldera received "with enormous gratitude."
</P>
<P>
At the Managua Embankment, the heads of state unveiled a bronze
statue of El Libertador Simon Bolivar donated by the Venezuelan
government to Nicaragua.
</P>
<P>
Bolivar, a 19th-century general, was in support of the unity of
Latin American countries and their independence from Spain.
</P>
</TEXT>
