<DOCNO> XIE19971217.0273 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukraine Destroys Nuclear Ballistic Missiles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine has destroyed 68 SS-19
intercontinental ballistic missiles (ICBMs) and 107 ICBM
launchers, a senior Ukrainian military official said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a news briefing, Nikolai Goncharenko, director of
the inspection center of the armed forces, said Ukraine plans to
further destroy 62 such missiles and 20 launching devices for
SS-24 ICBMs, the Ukrainian Interfax News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Under a joint statement signed by Russia, the United States and
Ukraine in 1991, Ukraine should destroy all the 180 SS-19 and 46
SS-24 missiles deployed within its territory by the former Soviet
Union.
</P>
<P>
The total number of conventional weapons deployed within
Ukraine does not exceed the limit set in the Treaty on
Conventional Armed Forces in Europe, the military official said.
</P>
<P>
According to the treaty signed between the 16-nation North
Atlantic Treaty Organization and six former member states of the
Warsaw Pact, Ukraine is allowed to have 4,800 tanks and 5,050
armored vehicles in its arsenal.
</P>
<P>
Goncharenko also denied the possibility of utilizing the
launching devices for agricultural or industrial purposes.
</P>
</TEXT>
