<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thai National Carrier to Sell 335 Million Shares </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Thai Airways International is
planning to sell 335 million shares as part of the government's
privatization program, a local newspaper reported today.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 235 million shares are from the Finance Ministry
which owns 93 percent of the national carrier, the Bangkok Post
said.
</P>
<P>
The rest 100 million shares to be sold will be new shares, the
newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Some 85 percent of the total shares are likely to be marketed
on overseas markets if the new board of the carrier, which will
take office on Friday, approves the privatization plan, the
newspaper added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
