<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Tamil Inmates Continue Fast in Prison </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 17 (Xinhua) -- About 350 Sri Lankan Tamil
rebel prisoners in a jail in Kalutara, 43 kilometers south of
Colombo, continued their fast for the fourth consecutive day
Tuesday to protest against the killing of three other non-Sinhala
inmates by Sinhala prisoners.
</P>
<P>
Two Tamils and a Muslim were killed while clashing with some
Sinhala inmates in the same prison last Friday, police said here
today.
</P>
<P>
At least 17 others sustained major injuries during the clash,
which was started by the Sinhala inmates who launched an attack at
those Tamils.
</P>
<P>
Police said the Tamil inmates began fast last Saturday and
asked to be transferred to other prisons.
</P>
<P>
Police investigators have recorded statements of prison
officers who were on duty that day to find what role they had
played during the clash. Several persons involved in the clash
were also taken into custody. 
</P>
</TEXT>
