<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Promotes Sustainable Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 17 (Xinhua) -- Tourism experts called for
sustainable tourism development at a seminar that closed here
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
They urged department concerned to rationally and efficiently
explore tourism resources in China, protect the environment, and
promote the sustainable development of tourism at the two-day
seminar jointly held by the China National Tourism
Administration(CNTA), The State Science and Technology Commission
(SSTC) and the Chinese Academy of Sciences.
</P>
<P>
According to a survey conducted by the World Tourism
Organization, China will rank first in the world in the number of
overseas tourists with the arrival of 137 million in the year 2020.
</P>
<P>
However, although China is a big country endowed with rich
tourism resources, its per capita tourism resources are
insufficient, pointed out Liu Yanhua, an official with SSTC.
</P>
<P>
Statistics indicate that China's per capita forested area only
ranks 121 in the world. And its per capita beach resources are
lower than the average amount of the countries with seashores.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, an increasing number of tourists flock to
suburban scenic spots, and other well-known scenic sights, causing
overcrowding.
</P>
<P>
Due to the destructive exploration of the tourism resources in
some places, the deterioration of the ecology has constituted a
serious threat to the current and potential tourism resources. As
a result, the sustainable development of tourism in China should
attract the attention of all of the society, experts at the
seminar held.
</P>
<P>
In order to harmonize the exploration of tourism resources with
the protection and improvement of the ecology, CNTA has decided to
designate the year 1999 as the Ecological Tour Year, Zhong
Haisheng, deputy director of the CNTA Planning and Statistics
Department, told the seminar. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
