<HEADLINE> Large Power Project in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, December 17 (Xinhua) -- A 500-kilovolt power project
in China's Jiangsu Province, which costs 7.72 billion yuan, has
been approved by the World Bank and China's State Development Bank.
</P>
<P>
The project will involve five 500-kv transformer substations in
Yancheng, Yangzhou, Nantong, and Shibei and Shengpu, and expanding
two 500-kv substations in Changzhou and Nanjing for a combined
capacity of 5.5 million kv.
</P>
<P>
It will also mean 993 kilometers of 500-kv power transmission
lines, some of which go across the Yangtze between Jiangying and
Jingjiang.
</P>
<P>
This will greatly improve power supplies in Jiangsu's northern
and coastal parts and help meet energy needs in the province.
</P>
</TEXT>
