<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Caldera, Aleman Inaugurate Monument to Simon Bolivar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Venezuelan President Rafael
Caldera and his Nicaraguan counterpart Arnoldo Aleman on Tuesday
inaugurated a monument in memory of the South American hero Simon
Bolivar at the Managua Embankment.
</P>
<P>
Caldera arrived on Tuesday morning for a six-hour visit to
Nicaragua and was welcome by Aleman at the National Palace of
Culture before they held a private meeting.
</P>
<P>
Unveiling the statue, Aleman said, "This monument will remind
us of our need to see each other as brothers and not to forget
that only real unity can give the necessary strength for Latin
American countries to successfully face the challenges of the next
century."
</P>
<P>
He said that the monument to the El Libertador symbolizes
Bolivar's courage in the battle field and shows the figure of a
thinker who conceived the most beautiful project of Latin American
union.
</P>
<P>
"Bolivar today means the heroic determination to safeguard our
common place, which is America," Aleman said.
</P>
<P>
Managua mayor Roberto Cedeno thanked Venezuela for offering the
El Libertador's monument. 
</P>
