<HEADLINE> Peru's Fish Meal Export Grows </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Peru's fish meal export totaled
1.05 billion U.S. dollars this year, up 25 percent over 1996,
industry sources said today.
</P>
<P>
With the rise, the fish meal has become one of the country's
main export products.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, fish meal export earned 834 million dollars with a
total of 1.6 million tons sold abroad.
</P>
<P>
Jose Sarmiento, president of the National Fishing Society, said
that the export price of fish meal was 700 dollars per ton this
year, 35 percent higher than last year's 518 dollars. 
</P>
