<HEADLINE> BOC to Handle Loans for Power Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 17 (Xinhua) -- The State Development Bank of
China yesterday signed an agreement in Beijing to authorize the
Bank of China (BOC) to handle its 1.1 billion yuan (about 132.5
million US dollars) loan to a power project in Chongqing,
according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
According to the agreement, BOC will act as the agent bank
responsible for the issue and recalling of the loan while
supervising the use of the fund.
</P>
<P>
The loan will be used for the second phase of construction of
the Luohuang Power Plant in Chongqing, said a BOC official.
</P>
<P>
Involving a total investment of 4.76 billion yuan, the project
will build two thermal power generating units with 350,000
kilowatt capacity each.
</P>
<P>
The project will also include the construction of a
310-kilometer-long, 220-kilovolt power transmission line.
</P>
<P>
Upon completion at the end of next year, the power plant will
have an annual power generating capacity of 1.4 million kilowatts.
</P>
<P>
The plant will ease the electricity shortage in Chongqing and
be a powerful boost to its economic growth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
