<HEADLINE> Five Russian Swimmers Banned for Taking Drugs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Five Russian swimmers,
including an Olympic gold medalist, were suspended for taking
banned drugs by the swimming ruling body FINA in Lausanne on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Vladimir Pychenko, Olga Kochetkova and Natalia Mescheriakova
were each banned for two years for use of the anabolic steroid
Metandienone Metabolites, FINA said.
</P>
<P>
The bans were back-dated to go into effect Oct. 18, when the
three tested positive at a training camp in Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
A fourth swimmer, Olena Lapunova, was provisionally suspended
pending a hearing for use of the same steroid.
</P>
<P>
A fifth, Alexey Koleshnikov, was suspended for three months for
use of cannabis. His ban begins on January 1.
</P>
<P>
Pychnenko, 27, swam on the relay team which won the gold medal
and set a world record in the 4x200 freestyle at the Summer Games
in Barcelona. 
</P>
</TEXT>
