<HEADLINE> Brazil Edges Out Mexico from Confederations' Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT, December 16 (Xinhua) -- Brazil dashed Mexico's hope to
reach the semi-finals by winning 3-2 in a Confederations' Cup
soccer match in Riyadh on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The result left Brazil atop of group A with Australia second,
despite losing 1-0 earlier to Saudi Arabia. The two go through to
Friday's semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
Mexico needed a draw to qualify and played a defensive game for
the first 40 minutes when Pavel Pardo brought down Falvio
Conceicao and Romario converted the penalty.
</P>
<P>
Mexican Luis Hernandez set up an equalizer for Cuauhtemoc
Blanco at the 52nd minute.
</P>
<P>
But Brazil regained the lead when Mexican defender Fracisco
Gabriel missed a loose ball in his own penalty area and Denilson
snapped it up six minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Defender Junior Baiano added a third at the 64th minute.
</P>
<P>
Mexico pulled one goal back in the final minute when substitute
Ramon Ramirez curled a free-kick around the Brazilian wall into
the net. 
