<HEADLINE> Large Ancient Tomb Found in Shandong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 17 (Xinhua) -- A large ancient tomb dating 1,700
years was discovered in Qihe County, east China's Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The tomb, covering 2,500 square meters, has a central hall 3.2
meters high, with large slabstone ceilings supported by ten big
stone columns.
</P>
<P>
Surrounding the main hall are interior passages, with ancient
characters and paintings of human figures carved on walls, pillars
and stone doors.
</P>
<P>
Archaeologists concluded that the tomb was built in late
Eastern Han Dynasty (25-220 AD). It was proved to have high
archaeoloical value for its size and complicated structure.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
