<HEADLINE> Large Heart Gene Database Compiled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 16 (Xinhua) --The first large heart gene
database has been compiled by an international group of scientists
from China, The United States and Canada.
</P>
<P>
According to an AP report from Dallas, the database of 46,000
genes could be helpful to find better diagnosis and treatments for
cardiovascular diseases like high blood pressure and heart
attacks.
</P>
<P>
With four years' efforts, the scientists have identified about
80 percent of the genes that control the growth and development of
the heart and blood vessels, said the group leader C. C. Liew of
Toronto University.
</P>
<P>
They also unearthed those genes that lead to cardiovascular
abnormalities and disease.




