<DOCNO> XIE19971217.0339 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-12-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Coast Guard Rescues Sinking Freighter Crew </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 16 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. Coast Guard
helicopter rescued all the 10 members of the crew of a small
freighter which was sinking early today in storm-tossed seas off
the Florida coast.
</P>
<P>
The rescue about 88 kilometers southeast of Miami came as the
National Weather Service was warning Florida east coast residents
of "a very dangerous situation" caused by an Atlantic storm.
</P>
<P>
The vessel was taking on water after losing its engine shaft
and the crew was preparing to abandon ship into a four-man life
raft when the Coast Guard received a call for help from the
captain at 2:00 a.m. EST.
</P>
<P>
A rescue helicopter arrived in time to pluck the crew to safety
as the boat began foundering. 
</P>
</TEXT>
